        {
            "name": "Tiefling",
            "type": "section",
            "sections": [],
            "text": "Tieflings are planar scions with fiendish blood. One of the most common types is pitborn, who bear a demonic corruption infesting their mortal bloodline. Some strive to live above their forebear\u2019s fiendish reputation, but many, such as this tiefling adept, simply accept their label and delve fully into evil.<br/><br/><b><u><a aonid=\"5\" game-obj=\"Skills\" general=\"true\">Recall Knowledge - Humanoid</a></u> (<u><a aonid=\"14\" game-obj=\"Skills\">Society</a></u>)</b>: DC 18",
            "source": {
                "name": "Bestiary",
                "link": {
                    "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01y0m?Pathfinder-Bestiary"
                },
                "page": 262
            }
        },
        {
            "name": "Planar Scion",
            "type": "section",
            "sections": [
                {
                    "name": "Other Planar Scions",
                    "type": "sidebar",
                    "sections": [],
                    "text": "As many types of planar scions exist as planes of existence, and even then there are significant differences between scions depending on the exact nature of their extraplanar forebears. Angelic scions are known as aasimars, fiendish scions are called tieflings, and monitor scions are urobians.",
                    "source": {
                        "name": "Bestiary",
                        "link": {
                            "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01y0m?Pathfinder-Bestiary"
                        },
                        "page": 262
                    },
                    "subtype": "related_creatures",
                    "sidebar_heading": "Related Creatures",
                    "image": "Sidebar_4_RelatedCreatures.png"
                },
                {
                    "name": "Planar Origins",
                    "type": "sidebar",
                    "sections": [],
                    "text": "Most planar scions are the distant descendants of some immortal progenitor far back in the family\u2019s bloodline. Others, however, may be the result of powerful planar energies, magical curses, or even the intervention of a deity or demigod.",
                    "source": {
                        "name": "Bestiary",
                        "link": {
                            "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01y0m?Pathfinder-Bestiary"
                        },
                        "page": 262
                    },
                    "subtype": "additional_lore",
                    "sidebar_heading": "Additional Lore",
                    "image": "Sidebar_2_AdditionalLore.png"
                }
            ],
            "text": "Many immortals dwell upon the other planes of the Great Beyond. Some are benevolent and kindly, like angels. Others are cruel and destructive, like demons. And some flt roles outside of morality, like psychopomps. It\u2019s far from unheard of that mortals and immortals alike become entangled romantically, and the children of such engagements carry a supernatural element in their bloodlines for generations to follow. After the first generation, this otherworldly influence usually lies dormant, but now and then, the influence can manifest strongly in descendants many years later. These inheritors of extraplanar legacies are known collectively as planar scions.",
            "source": {
                "name": "Bestiary",
                "link": {
                    "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01y0m?Pathfinder-Bestiary"
                },
                "page": 262
            }
        }
    ],
